@ijuma Agreed this has quite a bit of things included. Generally in `.gitignore` files there are 2 categories, `global` and `project`. The `global` ignore settings are usually in your home git config and are related to your specific usage and environment. Things like os files, editor of choice files, etc. While the `project` ignore settings are just for project specific things like java artifacts, logs, etc.

In the case of Kafka, incrementally global ignore settings were slowly being added the the `.gitignore` file to prevent accidental checkins of IDE files, OS files, etc. Instead of slowly adding them one by one as issues were hit, I figured I would just add a relatively comprehensive list of safe ignores settings, global or not.

I also documented what each section of entries ignores putting the Kafka specific rules towards the bottom.
